'''Farès Ghedjemis''' (born 6 September 2002) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[forward (association football)|forward]] for Italian {{Italian football updater|Frosinone}} club [[Frosinone Calcio|Frosinone]]. Born in France, he plays for the [[Algeria national football team|Algeria national team]].

== Club career ==
Born in [[Montreuil, Seine-Saint-Denis|Montreuil]], [[Seine-Saint-Denis]], France,<ref name="ouest" /> Ghedjemis has Algerian origins.<ref name="ladepeche" /><ref name="dz">{{Cite web |last=D |first=Salim |date=2024-01-03 |title=Mercato : Ghedjemis signe en Serie A ! |url=https://www.dzfoot.com/?p=252196 |access-date=2024-01-05 |website=Football Algérien - DZFOOT.COM |language=fr-FR}}</ref> His mother is from Bejaïa and his father from Kenchela

Coming from a sports family including his father Khalid Ghedjemis, a former N2 player .Having started playing at [[Chelles, Seine-et-Marne|Chelles]], [[Seine-et-Marne]],<ref name="ouest-france2">{{Cite web |date=2023-03-18 |title=Football. Vannes OC : la trajectoire atypique de Farès Ghedjemis |url=https://www.ouest-france.fr/sport/football/vannes-oc/football-vannes-oc-la-trajectoire-atypique-de-fares-ghedjemis-d62267ee-c4d9-11ed-93d7-4c4cd65beb9c |access-date=2024-01-05 |website=Ouest-France |language=fr}}</ref> Ghedjemis is a youth product of [[ES Troyes AC|Troyes]] and [[Le Havre AC|Le Havre]].<ref name="ladepeche">{{Cite web |title=Football : d'une relégation en National 3 à la Serie A en six mois... La formidable ascension de Farès Ghedjemis, recrue de Frosinone |url=https://www.ladepeche.fr/2024/01/03/football-dune-relegation-en-national-3-a-la-serie-a-en-six-mois-la-formidable-ascension-de-fares-ghedjemis-recrue-de-frosinone-11675646.php |access-date=2024-01-05 |website=La Dépêche |language=fr}}</ref>

After playing with Le Havre's reserve team in [[Championnat National 3|National 3]], he started playing with the first teams of [[Évreux FC 27|Évreux]] and [[Vannes OC|Vannes]], both times in [[Championnat National 2|National 2]].<ref name="ouest" /><ref name="ladepeche" /><ref name="ouest-france2" /><ref name="pn">{{Cite web |last=Lenud |first=Victorien |date=2024-01-02 |title=Football – National : le FC Rouen officialise le départ de Ghedjemis, Bouzamoucha parti pour rester |url=https://www.paris-normandie.fr/id480341/article/2024-01-02/football-national-le-fc-rouen-officialise-le-depart-de-ghedjemis-bouzamoucha |access-date=2024-01-05 |website=Paris-Normandie |language=fr}}</ref>

In the summer 2023, after scoring 6 goals and delivering 6 assists in half a season for Vannes, he was part of the revelations of the [[2022–23 Championnat National 2|2022–23 National 2]], but was a free agent after his club suffered relegation to the fifth tier.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Transferts : Frosinone fonce sur Farès Ghedjemis (Rouen) |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Frosinone-fonce-sur-fares-ghedjemis-rouen/1438701 |access-date=2024-01-05 |website=L'Équipe |language=fr}}</ref> Despite being reportedly followed by several French professional leagues clubs,<ref>{{Cite web |last=Pardon |first=Jordan |date=2023-05-26 |title=Vannes : Farès Ghedjemis pisté en National 1 et en Ligue 2 |url=https://www.footmercato.net/a4332996781848409504-vannes-fares-ghedjemis-piste-en-national-1-et-en-ligue-2 |access-date=2024-01-05 |website=Foot Mercato |language=fr}}</ref> he joined [[2023–24 Championnat National|third division]] side [[FC Rouen]].<ref name="ladepeche" /><ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-01-02 |title=Rouen : Farès Ghedjemis file en Serie A et marque l'histoire du club (off) |url=https://www.foot-national.com/national/rouen-fares-ghedjemis-file-en-serie-a-et-marque-l-histoire-du-club-off-849499 |access-date=2024-01-05 |website=Foot National |language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Billeaud |first=M. |date=2023-11-24 |title=Bouzamoucha, A. Allée, Ghedjemis... Trois moteurs du FC Rouen |url=https://www.footnormand.fr/actualites/fc-rouen/bouzamoucha-a-allee-ghedjemis-trois-moteurs-du-fc-rouen/ |access-date=2024-01-05 |website=Foot Normand |language=fr-FR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Mehali |first=Sofiane |date=2023-06-12 |title=Mercato : Fares Ghedjemis signe au FC Rouen |url=https://www.dzfoot.com/?p=243431 |access-date=2024-01-05 |website=Football Algérien - DZFOOT.COM |language=fr-FR}}</ref>

In January 2024, he was transferred to [[Frosinone Calcio|Frosinone]] in [[2023–24 Serie A|Serie A]] for 300 000 euros, plus 10% of a potential future sale, making it already the record transfer for his [[Championnat National|French National]] club.<ref name="ladepeche" /><ref name="pn" /><ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-01-04 |title=Un joueur de National part en Serie A |url=https://www.sofoot.com/breves/un-joueur-de-national-part-en-serie-a |access-date=2024-01-05 |website=So Foot |language=fr}}</ref> He signed a 2-years contract with the Italian side.<ref name="ouest">{{Cite web |last=Burban |first=Quentin |date=2024-01-03 |title=Mercato. Du National 2 à la Serie A en six mois : la folle ascension de Farès Ghedjemis |url=https://www.ouest-france.fr/sport/football/transferts/mercato-du-national-2-a-la-serie-a-en-six-mois-la-folle-ascension-de-fares-ghedjemis-d98e29dc-aa47-11ee-ad44-c03d56c454d6 |access-date=2024-01-05 |website=Ouest-France |language=fr}}</ref>

==International career==
Born in France, Ghedjemis is of Algerian descent. He was called up to the [[Algeria national football team|Algeria national team]] for a set of friendlies in March 2026.<ref>{{cite web|title=Algeria: Petkovic's squad announced with 6 new faces!|url=https://foot-africa.com/en/news/algeria-petkovics-squad-announced-with-6-new-faces-1130582/|website=Foot-Africa.com|date=18 March 2026|access-date=22 March 2026}}</ref> He debuted with Algeria in a 7–0 friendly win over [[Guatemala national football team|Guatemala]] on 27 March 2026, and scored his side's 6th goal.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.el-balad.com/16894198|title=Algérie – Guatemala en direct: Zidane écarté, Mastil titulaire à Gênes - El-Balad.com}}</ref>

== Style of play ==
A left-footed [[forward (association football)#Winger|winger]], Ghedjemis can play on both wings, with a preference for the right side on his inverted foot.<ref name="dz" />

He was compared to his fellow Le Havre graduate [[Riyad Mahrez]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-11-24 |title=Farès Ghedjemis, le dynamiteur du FC Rouen |url=https://www.footnormand.fr/fil-actualites/fares-ghedjemis-le-dynamiteur-du-fc-rouen/ |access-date=2024-01-05 |website=Foot Normand |language=fr-FR}}</ref>

